Package functions

Class FactorNexus

  • java.lang.Object
    • functions.FunctionPart
      • functions.Nexus
        • functions.FactorNexus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class FactorNexus
extends Nexus
    Class representing a multiplication of multiple FunctionParts
    This function is constructed like following: f(x) = u(x) * v(x) * ...
    Returns always null for Nexus.getAntiderivative().
    Author:
    Jonathan Brose, Nick Dressler
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getString

        public java.lang.String getString​(int i,
                                  java.lang.String variableName)
        Description copied from class: FunctionPart
        Returns the function term as String.
        Specified by:
        getString in class Nexus
        Parameters:
        i - :
        • if i > 0 the String starts with "+" or "-" depending on factor a.
          if i=0 only "-" will be added (if a is negative) so if the a is positive nothing will be added in front of the value.
          For example:
          • -4x^2
            if i < 0 the String is like if i > 0, but with a space between.
          For example:
          • - 4x^2 oder + 4x^2
        variableName -
        • Name of the variable used to calculate the function
          For example:
          • f(vName) = vName^2
        Returns:
        the function term as String.

      • getChainingString

        public java.lang.String[] getChainingString​(int i)
        Description copied from class: FunctionPart
        This method is essential for Chaining.getString(int, String). Works almost like FunctionPart.getString(int, String), but itÂ´s split at the variableName and both sides get stored in the array.
        Specified by:
        getChainingString in class FunctionPart
        Parameters:
        i - :
        • if i > 0 the String starts with "+" or "-" depending on factor a.
          if i=0 only "-" will be added (if a is negative) so if the a is positive nothing will be added in front of the value.
          For example:
          • -4x^2
            if i < 0 the String is like if i > 0, but with a space between.
          For example:
          • - 4x^2 oder + 4x^2
        Returns:
        an array with the String left and right from the variable.
        For example:
        • for -2x^3 the method returns ["-2x("; ")^3"]
        Now the inner function String can be inserted between this parts.
        For example:
        • -2x(sin(4))^3

      • sumUpFactors

        public void sumUpFactors()
        Multiplies the factors of all FunctionParts in functionParts to one product. Then sets the product as factor of the first FunctionPart.
        For Example:
        • functionParts: 3*sin(x) *4x2 *1,5ex
        Results in:
        • functionParts: 18*sin(x) *x2 *ex

      • sumUp

        private void sumUp()
        If this FactorNexus contains other FactorNexuses, this method takes all FunctionParts contained by the other FactorNexuses and moves them into this FactorNexus

        For Example:
        • FaktorVerknuepfung.fucntionParts[FactorNexus[Sin , PowerFunction], ExponentialFunction]
        • "(Sin * PowerFunction) * ExponentialFunction"
        results in:
        • FaktorVerknuepfung.functionParts[Sin, PowerFunction, ExponentialFunction]
        • "Sin * PowerFunction * ExponentialFunction"

      • containsFactorNexus

        private boolean containsFactorNexus()
        checks whether this FactorNexus contains other FactorNexuses or not.
        Returns:
        - true if contains other FactorNexuses, otherwise false
